<font color="#FF0000">COMMENTS FOR CHRIS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Mar 11 22:17:15 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chris,<br><br>
Thanks for taking the time to read everything on this post. It is a real challenge of endurance. Thanks also for your honesty and caring. There are many, many points of view here. It is not often, however, that we are honored by the points of view of someone who has had no connection whatever with the Vietnam War. You have taken the time to weigh the debate and present views of honest consideration of feelings and convictions from a fresh vantage.<br><br>
I am a Vietnam Veteran who is on an exploration of fundimental issues, ideas, and feelings as part of a process of acknowlegement, healing, and reconcilliation. I find your words echoed by others who were historically involved in the Vietnam vortex. Your words lend credibility to some issues that are difficult for me to see clearly and accept. I must therefore consider these issues with greater care. <br><br>
It is unimportant if eventually we agree or disagree on one point or another. It is very important that we use a process of honest consideration.<br><br>
I encourage you to examine other topics on this page. Your points of view will be appreciated and may very well encourage continued healthy debate on issues important to all of us.<br><br>
Thanks again for you points of view. You are as welcome to contribute at any time as it is with everyone now here.<br><br>
Arthur <br><br>
   
